abstract: Mr. Esper, a former soldier and lobbyist for Raytheon, takes over at the Pentagon after its longest period without a permanent leader.
snippet: Mr. Esper, a former soldier and lobbyist for Raytheon, takes over at the Pentagon after its longest period without a permanent leader.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate overwhelmingly confirmed Mark T. Esper as secretary of defense on Tuesday, ending the longest period by far that the Pentagon had been without a permanent leader.

abstract: The Democratic National Committee has all but encouraged performative breakout moments, and candidates must try to go viral or risk being left behind.

headline_main: Why the Democratic Debates Are Starting to Feel Like a Reality Show
headline_print_headline: Candidates Are Pushed to Go Viral, or Risk Being Left Behind

abstract: Kamala Harris and Joe Biden will face off again on the debate stage later this month, and Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren will headline the other half of the two-night event.
snippet: Kamala Harris and Joe Biden will face off again on the debate stage later this month, and Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren will headline the other half of the two-night event.
lead_paragraph: [Half of the field might be onstage for the last time in this election. Here’s our latest coverage.]

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Democrats still don’t agree on why they lost the White House in 2016. But they have absolutely no intention of repeating their mistakes.

abstract: Dangerously hot temperatures are predicted from Oklahoma to New England. Here’s the forecast, with some tips on staying safe.
snippet: Dangerously hot temperatures are predicted from Oklahoma to New England. Here’s the forecast, with some tips on staying safe.
lead_paragraph: BOSTON — Dangerously high temperatures are expected to spread across the Central and Eastern United States on Wednesday through the weekend, with temperatures soaring above 100 degrees Fahrenheit in the hardest-hit places, the National Weather Service has warned.
